The Telegraph - Calcutta : International
 Tuesday, May 25, 2004 				 Powell apology for prison abuse
																								Copenhagen, May 24 (Reuters): US secretary of state Colin Powell published today a written apology for the abuse of Iraqi prisoners at the Abu Ghraib military prison, saying he would see that justice was done.																								Powells remarks were published in a letter in the Danish daily Politiken, just days before parliament was to decide whether to extend the presence of Danish troops in Iraq.																								Denmark is part of the coalition that invaded Iraq to topple dictator Saddam Hussain last year and its government has had wide support for keeping its soldiers in Iraq. 
